##Small Farm samples under the epidemic: "ONE-SIZE-FITS-ALL" road closure of agricultural supplies, no workers back to spring cultivation

Weixin Signal Wowjiemian

Function introduction, the interface news is China has the influence original financial and economic new media, only serves the independent thinking crowd

Photograph: Shi Yan

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
REPORTER: Editor Tang Jun: Shen Xiaoge

“

Many small farms have been affected by transport problems.

”

“

Many small farms have been affected by transport problems.

”

Only a few hundred Jin of rice stocks, some food has been sold out, this case a small e-commerce platform for agricultural products in two weeks at most normal operation, Stone Yan anxious bad.

Shi Yan is the owner of the "share the harvest" farm in Shunyi District, Beijing. She interned on a farm in the United States during her phd at Renmin University of China and returned to found China's first CSA (community-supported agriculture) farms.

At present, the farm has 400 mu of land under cultivation, the main crops are vegetables, and a small number of fruit trees, but also raised some poultry.

As the farm business matured, it began growing food in partnership with ecological smallholders elsewhere, or buying produce directly to sell to its own members and scattered consumers. Affected by the epidemic, many of the agricultural products can not be shipped out, the platform is facing the risk of total out of stock.

###Rice can't leave the village, pigs can't get into the slaughterhouse

There are about 150 products on the farm's e-commerce platform, from nearly 100 suppliers, and about half of them have shipping problems that make delivery impossible.

Shi Yan told interface news that supplies including rice from Five Confucian virtues, pork from Gansu, Lotus root from Tianjin, chestnuts from Huairou District, apples from Yantai, Sachima and biscuits from Yunnan could not be shipped.

Rice is one of the most scarce products, now only a few hundred pounds in stock, this week will be out of supply, other products can only maintain a maximum of two weeks of sales.

The farm's rice comes from Five Confucian virtues, Heilongjiang, and is grown in partnership with local farmer Wu Shu. Wu Shu told the interface news reporter that his village implemented traffic control, do not let villagers in and out at will, not to let trucks in and out, Rice can not be shipped out.

Uncle Wu's warehouse also has 20,000 Jin of rice, harvested around November last year. According to past experience, Rice sales basically end around the Spring Festival, if there is another month of rice shipped out, the back is also very difficult to sell.

The farm and Uncle Five's cooperation model is the advance payment, that is, the farm will advance the payment to uncle five, and participate in the rice planting process. If the rice does not sell out in the end, the loss will fall on Shi Yan.

Pork in Gansu has the same problem. Wu Ping runs a pig farm in Qingyang city in Gansu Province, where his village restricts the free movement of people and vehicles and has checkpoints on all roads to prevent pork from being shipped out.

Wu also told interface that he had another problem. A small slaughterhouse that had been used before had not been allowed to reopen, and large slaughterhouses do not slaughter pigs from small farmers, it also makes Wu Ping's business unsustainable.

Sharing Harvest Farm and Wu Ping's cooperation to take the order system, which means that if the pork unsalable, will give Wu Ping caused considerable losses.

Even if the road smooth place, because express delivery has not yet fully resumed, there are logistics distribution costs. Hebei's Sanhe Yushun farm supplies peanuts to the shared harvest farm. Now, only Shunfeng is open for business in the area. If the volume is large, the freight rate is at least twice that of the three-way express. Small farms at both ends of the logistics chain can not afford the sudden increase in costs.

In addition to members, individual customers patronize the farm micro shop every year tens of thousands of people, annual sales of five million yuan, if long time road transport can not be completely restored, it is expected to cause a lot of losses this year.

Many agricultural products sales and transportation also encountered a similar problem. Beijing, Changping District's strawberry base, which relies on annual visits around the Lunar New Year, is unable to organize the harvest this year and has struggled to find other sales channels. About 10,000 pounds of strawberries are not on sale in Changping District, according to interface news.

###Can't change the supplier

Every Spring Festival harvest-sharing farm will be closed for a period of time, usually to the eighth day of the resumption of distribution. This year due to the impact of the epidemic, in order to ensure that members continue to supply food, in the second day of the distribution, but soon found that out-of-town goods can not be delivered.

According to past experience, the demand for food distribution during the Spring Festival is not very high, so the farm does not have much in stock. Now everyone is at home to buy more demand, many varieties have been out of stock.

Originally Stone Yan expected the situation on the 15th of the first month will ease, so that the farm can survive a week or two normal business, but it is still unknown. It is also difficult to predict when full normal deliveries will be received, given that suppliers are involved in different parts of the country and the measures implemented vary from place to place.

The establishment of cooperation in organic agriculture is a long process. In the years before Uncle Wu grew rice for the farm, Shi Yan would often travel to Five Confucian virtues for supervision and testing, and his colleagues would also travel to Five Confucian virtues to work to ensure that the rice produced was up to standard. The pork of Gansu Wu Ping is the same, Shi Yan needs to understand the pig breeding process, Wu Ping needs to understand how to cut pork consumers most acceptable, both sides gradually run-in.

There were friends who were willing to provide pork, but the farm could not accept it. Based on food safety and organic standards, it is more important to build trust with suppliers, which means farms can not easily change sources of supply to fill current inventory gaps, Shi said.

The farm currently has about 1,200 members, and most are used to ordering from the farm based on trust. They also face the problem of re-sourcing if some of their produce goes out of supply.

Also, since vegetables are grown on their own farms, there is not much of a supply problem, but Labor is extremely scarce.

There are now more than 20 workers on the shared harvest farm, most of them from rural areas. Traffic is more restricted in some rural areas than in the cities, and with buses out of service, half the workers are trapped in their homes and unable to return.

Due to the shortage of manpower, members can choose their own side dishes have been changed to unified side dishes, which can save labor.

More importantly, if workers can no longer return to the farm, the production of home-grown vegetables will also be affected.

"The spring ploughing is about to start. We need to set up a big shed, sow, turn over the soil, fertilize and weed. If they don't return, these tasks will not be carried out normally and will directly affect the follow-up vegetable supply. " This is Shi Yan's biggest concern.

Vegetable supply is the main business of the farm, and agricultural production has a certain periodicity, if production can not keep up, subsequent farm operations will be more affected.

###The policy guarantee is expected to be put in place

As early as January 29, the Ministry of Transport issued a notice requiring transportation to be "one-stop-three-stop" , that is, to block the transmission channel of the virus, to ensure continuous road transport network, emergency transport green channel, the necessary mass production and living materials of the transport channel.

But many places, especially some rural areas have adopted a "one-size-fits-all" approach, the emergence of "hard isolation" , that is, a complete ban on people and goods in and out.

On February 11, at a press conference organized by the Joint Prevention and Control Mechanism of the State Council, Xu Yahua, director of the Transportation Service Department of the Ministry of Communications, mentioned that in the early days of the epidemic prevention and control, some places adopted measures such as road closures and vehicles being persuaded to return, it has played a certain role in controlling the spread of the epidemic, but at the same time, it has brought some inconvenience to the normal life of the people, the transportation of materials and the return of migrant workers.

Xu Yahua once again stressed that all places should strictly implement the "one break three continuous" and the "five strict prohibitions" , and make it clear that during the epidemic prevention and control period, necessities such as grain, oil, meat, poultry, eggs, milk, fruits and vegetables should be brought into the scope of emergency transportation.

"large-scale production bases such as Shouguang in Shandong may be better for external transportation, and small-and medium-sized farmers or agricultural producers are more affected in transportation, " Shi said. She understands that in addition to the farmers who supply themselves, many small farms are affected by transportation problems and are waiting for transportation and logistics to return to normal as soon as possible.

(Wu Ping is a pseudonym)
